\sec(\theta) d\theta = \pm d(x^2)
d(log(\sec(\theta) + \tan(\theta))) = \pm d(x^2)
log(\sec(\theta) + \tan(\theta)) = \pm (x^2 + k)
\sec(\theta) + \tan(\theta) = \exp(\pm (x^2 + k))
